Title: Bosonic Open Strings in a Tachyonic Background Field
Authors: Tasneem Zehra Husain and Maxim Zabzine (Stockholm University)
Comments: 13 pages. Talk presented at the Nordic Network On String Theory held
  at the Niels Bohr Institute, Copenhagen in May 2000
Report-no: USITP-00-07
\\
  We study a bosonic open string coupled to a tachyonic background field $T[X]$
and find that the tachyon field can effectively be replaced by a configuration
of D-branes placed at either the zeros or the critical points of $T[X]$,
depending on our choice of boundary conditions. This dual picture of the open
string tachyon is explored in detail for the explicit case when the tachyonic
field is quadratic.
